    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Marmite </strong>and <strong>onion marmalade </strong>to the pan with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p>",
