    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>Tenderstem</strong> <strong>broccoli </strong>to a pot and cover with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Return the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat with the <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>mustard mash</strong></p>",
